<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="426" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,469,1087,1147]" box="[151,288,1122,1147]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,279,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[175,1431,226,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Univagris tenebra sp. nov. 1. Dorsal habitus, 2. Lateral habitus, 3. Pronotum, 4. Face, 5. Pygofer, 6–8. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral, ventral, 9. Style, 10. Subgenital plate, valve and style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Figs. 1–10</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1194,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
Brown ochraceous, vertex slightly depressed on disc, with a median stripe bifid apically. Eyes black. Pronotum with linear brown mottling. Scutellum with a lateral brownish subtriangular spot. Fore wings hyaline with irregular dark brown mottling (
<figureCitation box="[396,504,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[175,1431,226,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Univagris tenebra sp. nov. 1. Dorsal habitus, 2. Lateral habitus, 3. Pronotum, 4. Face, 5. Pygofer, 6–8. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral, ventral, 9. Style, 10. Subgenital plate, valve and style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1194,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
Crown with anterior margin angulary produced. Pronotum slightly shorter than wide, anterior margin strongly produced, posterior margin slightly concave, length almost equal to combined length of mesoscutum and scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[159,265,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[175,1431,226,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Univagris tenebra sp. nov. 1. Dorsal habitus, 2. Lateral habitus, 3. Pronotum, 4. Face, 5. Pygofer, 6–8. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral, ventral, 9. Style, 10. Subgenital plate, valve and style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1194,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,369,1410,1435]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer lobe trapezoidal, 1.6X longer than wide, stout macrosetae over posterior half (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1422,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[175,1431,226,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Univagris tenebra sp. nov. 1. Dorsal habitus, 2. Lateral habitus, 3. Pronotum, 4. Face, 5. Pygofer, 6–8. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral, ventral, 9. Style, 10. Subgenital plate, valve and style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Valve 2.4X wide at base as long. Subgenital plate triangular, 2.9X long as broad at base, with lateral row of hairlike setae covering more than half of outer margin (
<figureCitation box="[733,817,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[175,1431,226,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Univagris tenebra sp. nov. 1. Dorsal habitus, 2. Lateral habitus, 3. Pronotum, 4. Face, 5. Pygofer, 6–8. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral, ventral, 9. Style, 10. Subgenital plate, valve and style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Style robust, cephalic arm broad and long, apophysis widened gradually at apex (
<figureCitation box="[460,527,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[175,1431,226,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Univagris tenebra sp. nov. 1. Dorsal habitus, 2. Lateral habitus, 3. Pronotum, 4. Face, 5. Pygofer, 6–8. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral, ventral, 9. Style, 10. Subgenital plate, valve and style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Connective arms touching each other, distal process with rounded lateral flange basally, acuminate distally, 1.6X as long as connective basad of articulation point with aedeagus, in lateral view apex slightly curved ventrally. Aedeagus simple, blunt at apex, shaft directed caudad at base, gradually curving dorsally with well developed dorsal apodeme, shaft closely appressed towards ventral process, gonopore apical, preatrium directed anteroventrad below shaft (
<figureCitation box="[670,778,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[175,1431,226,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Univagris tenebra sp. nov. 1. Dorsal habitus, 2. Lateral habitus, 3. Pronotum, 4. Face, 5. Pygofer, 6–8. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral, ventral, 9. Style, 10. Subgenital plate, valve and style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Figs. 6–8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1194,2011]" box="[199,1202,1698,1723]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,455,1698,1723]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Measurements (mm):</emphasis>
Male 3.9 long, 1.09 wide across eyes, 1.17 wide across pronotum.
</paragraph>
