<subSubSection box="[199,1396,1842,1867]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1194,2011]" box="[199,1396,1842,1867]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1842,1867]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Etymology:</emphasis>
The species name (Latin: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rajgopal &amp; Meshram" authorityYear="2018" box="[633,719,1842,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Univagris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebra">
<emphasis box="[633,719,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">tenebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning dark) alludes to the dark body color of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="426" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1194,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1878,1903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[801,919,1878,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Univagris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[801,919,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">U. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following (features of 
<taxonomicName box="[1284,1402,1878,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Univagris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[1284,1402,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">U. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parentheses): subgenital plate without stout setae submarginally (with 5–6 stout submarginal macrosetae) (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1422,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[175,1431,226,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Univagris tenebra sp. nov. 1. Dorsal habitus, 2. Lateral habitus, 3. Pronotum, 4. Face, 5. Pygofer, 6–8. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral, ventral, 9. Style, 10. Subgenital plate, valve and style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
), aedeagus blunt at apex, with well developed dorsal apodeme, shaft closely appressed towards ventral process, preatrium 
<date box="[267,315,1987,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" value="2010-10">10X</date>
shorter than in 
<taxonomicName box="[491,604,1986,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Univagris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[491,604,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">U. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[619,728,1986,2011]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[175,1431,226,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Univagris tenebra sp. nov. 1. Dorsal habitus, 2. Lateral habitus, 3. Pronotum, 4. Face, 5. Pygofer, 6–8. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral, ventral, 9. Style, 10. Subgenital plate, valve and style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Figs. 6–8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
